						               													<description>Spirax is played on a board of concentric circles. The circles have paths connecting them which spiral inwards towards the central vortex.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has four pieces which start along one spiral. Each turn the pieces can be moved by allocating movement points, with movement becoming more expensive the closer a piece is to the vortex. In addition, on some turns every piece on the board will move one space closer to the vortex.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pieces can attack others by moving over them. The result of a successful attack is to send the defending piece in towards the vortex. Pieces which enter the vortex re-appear along the edge. The object of the game is to make a certain number of successful attacks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
